node.title: Man charged with manslaughter and endangerment over death of 3yo girl found in drain
node.alt: blurred image of children sitting on bed near window
node.description: Police in North Queensland say they were called to a house where two young children were reported missing. A two-year-old was found safe and well, wandering in a street, while the three-year-old girl was found in a stormwater drain at about 8:20pm.
node.content: ["A 27-year-old man has been charged over the death of a toddler in Townsville yesterday.", "At around 6:40pm last night, emergency services were alerted to two missing children in the suburb of Kelso.", "A two-year-old was found uninjured, wandering a nearby street.", "The second child, a three-year-old girl, was found in a storm drain at 8:20pm and was taken to hospital where she was pronounced dead.", "Police charged the man, who was known to the children, with manslaughter, endangering children by exposure and driving under the influence of a drug.", "He was denied bail and will face Townsville Magistrates Court tomorrow."]
